Director in the Inspectorate Office of the Accountant-General of the Federation (OAGF), Mr. Anamekwe Chukwunyere Nwabuoku, has been drafted to take over the functions of the suspended Accountant-General of the Federation (AG-F), Ahmed Idris. Idris, who was arrested by operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) over alleged N80 billion fraud, is undergoing interrogation at the agency’s Abuja headquarters. He was suspended from office last week by a memo from the Finance, Budget and National Planning Minister Mrs Zainab, with a warning not “to attend to your place of work or contact any official in your Office except for any disciplinary hearing that may be advised”. Yesterday, Anamekwe was named to oversee the Office of the OAGF.   Drama, clashes, upsets at PDP Reps, Assembly primaries     ADC candidate to voters: shun moneybags     Firms, businesses await CBN’s decision on rates   A letter from the Permanent Secretary (Finance), Federal Ministry of Finance, Budget and National Planning Mr Aliyu Ahmed, said “the appointment is pending the outcome of the investigation”. A statement from the Finance Ministry asked Anamekwe to carry out his duty in strict compliance with extant rules and observe the highest sense of professionalism expected of an officer working at his level. Anamekwe from Ehime Mbano Local Government Area of Imo State was born on October 15, 1962. He holds a Higher National Diploma (HND) in Accountancy from the Institute of Management and Technology (IMT) Enugu, and Master of Science (M.Sc) in Financial Management from Common Wealth University, Belize.